node.text: Welcome back to Food for Mood! Head to the link in our bio for the full recipe along with even more content from our collaboration – and don't miss out on your chance to redeem a one-month free trial of Headspace! #WFMxHeadspace These statements have not been evaluated by the FDA. node.text: In the zone, on a roll, all systems go — today on “Focused” — the latest episode in our Food for Mood series with @headspace — we’re helping you harness these moments of peak clarity through the power of food. Just in time for World Vegan Day, Chef Chloe Coscarelli showed us how to make a Vegan Pumpkin Marble Cake! It's the perfect addition to @chefchloe’s Vegan Meal for 2 -- available to order now on shop.wfm.com (link in bio!). Get the recipe for the cake below! #WFMxChefChloe #Sponsored

Vegan Pumpkin Marble Cake (Makes 1 loaf)
Ingredients: 
- 2 cups 365 All-Purpose Flour 
- 1 cup 365 Organic Cane Sugar 
- 1 teaspoon 365 Baking Powder
- 1 teaspoon sea salt
- ½ teaspoon 365 Baking Soda
- 1 tablespoon pumpkin pie spice
- 1 cup canned pumpkin puree (or sweet potato puree)
- 1 cup 365 unsweetened Coconut Cream, mixed well before measuring
- ½ cup 365 Organic Coconut Oil, melted
- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar 
- 1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract
- 3 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder
- ½ cup vegan chocolate chips (optional)
- 365 Non-Dairy Plant-Based whipped cream or powdered sugar, for topping

Instructions:
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a large loaf pan and/or line with parchment. 

Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda, and pumpkin pie spice. In another bowl, whisk together pumpkin puree, coconut cream, coconut oil, vinegar, and vanilla. Pour the wet mixture into the dry mixture and whisk until just combined (don’t overmix!). 

Transfer ½ cup batter into a small bowl and stir in cocoa powder and 2 tablespoons water until incorporated. 

Fill the prepared pan with alternating dollops of pumpkin batter and chocolate batter. Sprinkle in chocolate chips, if using. Using a thin knife or chopstick, gently swirl the chocolate batter into the pumpkin batter. Bake for ~60 minutes. Let cool and slice. Top each slice with 365 by Whole Foods Market Non-Dairy Whipped Cream or powdered sugar.

node.text: 🚨Check the ice cream aisle🚨With new exclusive flavors that meet our standards, it’s a sweet summer haven with no high-fructose corn syrup. #wholefoodsmarket

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on July 11, 2021 tagging @taylorgolub. May be an image of food.

node.text: The sunny side of Sunday is brunch food ☀️ Elevate your brunch with @taylorgolub’s Pesto Eggs Sandwich. A perfectly fried egg topped with cheddar cheese, sliced avocado and, of course, pesto. Head to their page for the recipe. #wholefoodsmarket

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on July 10, 2021 tagging @jenisicecreams. May be an image of gelato and icecream.

node.text: What we’re high-fiving today: our new and exclusive flavor made by @jenisicecreams! Comment below with a guess on what candy bar inspired this flavor. Then, go enjoy 35% off any ice cream 7/7 - 7/20. Plus, Prime members get an extra 10% off. Restrictions apply.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on July 09, 2021 tagging @grandbabycakes. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Looking to end your week on a sweet note? We’re wild for @grandbabycakes’ icebox cake inspired by our 365 Frosted Animal Cookies. #WFMNewScoop #sponsored

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on July 08, 2021 tagging @eitan. May be an image of gelato.

node.text: Double tap if you're now craving @eitan’s ultimate ice cream sundae inspired by our 365 Midnight Double Feature Trail Mix. It’s the perfect sweet and salty combo, and with your vote, it can become a Whole Foods Market ice cream flavor! Share your vote in the comments of our last post before tomorrow, 7/9, and check back next week to see if this flavor makes the final two. #WFMNewScoop #sponsored

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on July 07, 2021. May be an image of food and text that says '1. FROSTED ANIMAL COOKIES'.

node.text: We all scream … for NEW ice cream! We want YOU to help us develop an exclusive Whole Foods Market ice cream that will hit our freezers next year. Vote in the comments before Friday, 7/9 with your pick's corresponding emoji: 1. 🐑 2. 🥜 3. 🎂 or 4. 🍒. Make sure to tune back in next week to see if your fave made the final two. #WFMNewScoop
